Overview
Dynamic frontend components play a key role in making the Furniture & Crockery Marketplace interactive, user-friendly, and responsive. 
These components ensure a seamless shopping experience by dynamically updating based on user actions and backend data.

Objectives
✅ Build dynamic components for essential marketplace features.
✅ Ensure reusability and efficiency in component design.
✅ Improve interactivity and responsiveness for a polished user experience.

Key Dynamic Components
🛋️ Product List Component
🔹 Dynamically displays furniture & crockery products fetched from the API.
🔹 Includes filters for categories, price range, and ratings.
🔹 Shows loading indicators while fetching data.

🛒 Cart Component
🔹 Updates in real-time when users add or remove items.
🔹 Displays total price, item quantity, and product details.
🔹 Seamlessly integrates with the checkout flow.

👤 User Profile Component
🔹 Shows user order history, saved items, and profile details.
🔹 Updates dynamically when users edit their profiles.
🔹 Ensures secure handling of personal data.

🔔 Notifications/Alerts Component
🔹 Provides real-time feedback (e.g., "Item added to cart").
🔹 Supports success, error, and warning messages.
🔹 Uses animations for a smooth user experience.

Implementation Tips
🚀 State Management: Use Redux or Context API to manage global state.
📱 Responsive Design: Ensure mobile-friendly layouts using Tailwind CSS.
⚡ Performance Optimization: Use React memoization to prevent unnecessary re-renders.

Notes
🔹 Test all components to ensure smooth API integration.
🔹 Use mock data for initial development before connecting to APIs.
🔹 Prioritize accessibility to make the marketplace user-friendly for all.

Conclusion
Dynamic frontend components are essential for building an engaging and modern Furniture & Crockery Marketplace. By focusing on reusability, responsiveness, 
and seamless API integration, these components enhance the overall user experience.

